<title>
Rear Lamp House Panel Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
The figure below shows condition where following parts are removed.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Front fender 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A9A06005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Back panel 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A9B06021"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0165.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.757mm" ver = "03" gw = "227" gh = "122"/>
</figure>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A9B06024001">
<title>
General Notes
</title>
<ptxt>
Welding method and number of welding points are the same on both sides. This repair instruction shows procedure for left side.
</ptxt>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A9B06024002" page = "2">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots and remove rear lamp house panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0148.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "71.168mm" ver = "01" gw = "226" gh = "185"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A9B06024003" page = "2">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before conducting any weld, check installation position and condition for installation part(s). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A9B04005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear lamp house panel.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld and plug weld.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0149.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "71.168mm" ver = "02" gw = "226" gh = "185"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
